    id: "en-tox-048", stem: "A 68-year-old male taking clopidogrel and aspirin presents to the ED with severe epistaxis refractory to anterior nasal packing. His platelet count is normal at 225,000/mm3 but platelet function is impaired. Which intervention should the nurse prepare?",
    options: ["Desmopressin (DDAVP) 0.3 mcg/kg IV to enhance platelet adhesion and consider platelet transfusion", "Tranexamic acid only", "Protamine sulfate infusion", "Vitamin K 10 mg IV"],
